0be%20prosecuted.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EOnly%20two%20corporations%20received%20declinations%20during%20Trump's%20term%20so%20far%20while%20facing%20investigations.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EA%20lawyer%20for%20a%20space%20research%20company%20explained%20to%20Business%20Insider%20how%20they%20pulled%20it%20off.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-officials-first-100-days-doge-deportations-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ETrump%20administration%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Justice%20Department%20officials%20have%20made%20clear%20in%20speeches%20and%20policy%20documents%20that%20they%20do%20not%20want%20to%20prosecute%20corporations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%2C%20so%20far%2C%20only%20two%20companies%20have%20received%20the%20gold%20star%20craved%20by%20every%20white-collar%20defense%20lawyer%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcompanies-self-report-crime-misconduct-justice-department-policy-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EA%20declination%20letter%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20April%2C%20Justice%20Department%20officials%20issued%20a%20letter%20and%20press%20release%20announcing%20that%20it%20was%20declining%20to%20prosecute%20the%20Universities%20Space%20Research%20Association%20after%20an%20employee%20illegally%20sold%20sensitive%20aviation%20software%20developed%20by%20the%20US%20military%20to%20a%20Chinese%20university.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20letter%2C%20addressed%20to%20USRA%20lawyer%20Clark%20Kent%20Ervin%2C%20praised%20the%20company's%20%26quot%3Bexceptional%20and%20proactive%20cooperation%2C%26quot%3B%20including%20swiftly%20disclosing%20the%20wrongdoing%2C%20improving%20internal%20controls%2C%20and%20firing%20Jonathan%20Soong%2C%20the%20employee.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20declination%20letter%20to%20USRA%20is%20one%20of%20only%20two%20issued%20by%20the%20second%20Trump%20administration%2C%20and%20it%20can%20serve%20as%20a%20case%20study%20in%20how%20companies%20can%20achieve%20the%20best-case%20outcome%20in%20the%20face%20of%20a%20Justice%20Department%20investigation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20an%20organization%20like%20USRA%20finds%20potentially%20illegal%20conduct%20from%20one%20of%20its%20employees%2C%20it%20has%20a%20choice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20could%20tell%20the%20Justice%20Department%20%E2%80%94%20and%20potentially%20face%20years%20of%20legal%20headaches%20and%20bad%20publicity%20as%20the%20government%20does%20its%20own%20investigation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOr%20it%20could%20handle%20things%20internally%2C%20blame%20individual%20bad%20apples%2C%20and%20keep%20quiet%20while%20hoping%20the%20government%20doesn't%20notice%20before%20the%20statute%20of%20limitations%20expires.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EErvin%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20USRA's%20management%20%26quot%3Bfully%20understood%20the%20perils%26quot%3B%20of%20disclosing%20criminal%20activity%20to%20the%20Justice%20Department%2C%20but%20didn't%20hesitate%20to%20do%20so%20anyway.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20recommended%20that%20USRA%20voluntarily%20self-disclose%20it%2C%20which%20the%20company%20properly%20did%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Ervin%2C%20an%20attorney%20at%20Squire%20Patton%20Boggs.%20%26quot%3BThere%20was%20no%20hesitancy%20whatsoever%20about%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226f2704df-2cc1-4357-b6de-9a886121dd1e%5C%22%3EThe%20secret%20software%20sale%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202017%2C%20Jonathan%20Soong%20received%20his%20email%20in%20his%20inbox%20that%20would%20upend%20his%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20time%2C%20Soong%20managed%20software%20sales%20at%20the%20USRA%2C%20which%20manages%20space%20and%20aviation%20research%20and%20educational%20programs%20across%20a%20consortium%20of%20universities%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20Soong's%20job%20was%20administering%20a%20US%20Army%20contract%20to%20sell%20sophisticated%20flight%20software.%20Most%20of%20the%20customers%20were%20American%20universities%20studying%20aeronautics%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20occasional%20aerospace%20company%20and%20defense%20contractor.%20But%20in%202017%2C%20Soong%20received%20an%20email%20from%20a%20representative%20of%20Beihang%20University%20in%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Beijing-based%20university%20was%20on%20a%20US%20government%20list%20of%20entities%20forbidden%20from%20receiving%20the%20software%2C%20in%20part%20because%20it%20develops%20rockets%20and%20drones%20in%20a%20way%20deemed%20contrary%20to%20%26quot%3Bnational%20security%20or%20foreign%20policy%20interests%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20US%20government%20court%20filings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESoong%20initially%20told%20the%20Beihang%20University%20representative%20as%20much%2C%20saying%20that%20%26quot%3Bred%20flags%26quot%3B%20prevented%20him%20from%20selling%20the%20software%20to%20them%2C%20prosecutors%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Beihang%20University%20representative%20developed%20a%20workaround.%20They%20used%20a%20third-party%20corporate%20entity%2C%20called%20Beijing%20Rainbow%20Technical%20Development%20Ltd.%2C%20to%20buy%20the%20software%2C%20prosecutors%20said.%20Soong%20approved%20the%20sale%2C%20and%20Beihang%20University%20soon%20had%20access%20to%20the%20closely%20guarded%20piece%20of%20technology%3Cstrong%3E.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20scheme%20went%20undetected%20for%20years%2C%20until%20USRA%20administrators%20stumbled%20upon%20records%20of%20the%20sale%20while%20reviewing%20its%20compliance%20with%20a%20different%20part%20of%20the%20NASA%20contract%2C%20Ervin%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUSRA%20administrators%20and%20Ervin%20opened%20an%20internal%20investigation.%20After%20several%20rounds%20of%20questioning%2C%20Soong%20came%20clean.%20He%20admitted%20to%20selling%20the%20software%20to%20Beihang%20University%20and%20personally%20pocketing%20the%20proceeds%20from%20other%20software%20sales.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20were%20looking%20%E2%80%94%20was%20there%20any%20other%20employee%3F%20Was%20there%20any%20officer%3F%20Was%20there%20any%20board%20member%20of%20USRA%20involved%20in%20this%3F%26quot%3B%20Ervin%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20we%20determined%20that%20he%20was%20a%20lone%20wolf%2C%20he%20was%20a%20rogue%20employee.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUSRA%20administrators%20viewed%20the%20company%20as%20a%20victim%20of%20Soong%2C%20and%20they%20believed%20the%20Justice%20Department%20would%20understand%20that%20he%20operated%20independently%2C%20Ervin%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20USRA%20had%20nothing%20to%20hide%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20company%20itself%20was%20not%20involved%20in%20this.%20This%20was%20a%20lone%20actor.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20USRA%20made%20multiple%20disclosures%20to%20the%20Justice%20Department%20and%20other%20government%20agencies%20over%20the%20course%20of%20its%2018-month%20internal%20investigation%2C%20Ervin%20said.%20Soong%20repaid%20%24161%2C000%20to%20the%20USRA%20and%20later%20pleaded%20guilty%20to%20criminal%20charges%20filed%20against%20him%2C%20court%20filings%20show.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20April%202023%2C%20a%20federal%20judge%20in%20San%20Francisco%20sentenced%20him%20to%2020%20months%20in%20prison.%20An%20attorney%20for%20Soong%20didn't%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22bf7edba3-65f6-4321-bdc6-97de0dc0b533%5C%22%3EHow%20to%20not%20get%20prosecuted%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDeclination%20letters%20have%20long%20been%20the%20gold%20standard%20for%20companies%20facing%20a%20DOJ%20investigation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20far%20better%20alternative%20to%20a%20criminal%20case%2C%20which%20could%20destroy%20a%20company%2C%20or%20even%20a%20non-prosecution%20agreement%2C%20which%20can%20still%20cast%20a%20cloud%20of%20suspicion%20on%20a%20corporation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20have%20basically%20good%20facts%20like%20this%2C%20you%20can%20get%20a%20non-prosecution%20agreement%2C%20meaning%20the%20government%20could%20prosecute%20you%2C%20but%20has%20chosen%20not%20to%2C%26quot%3B%20Ervin%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDeclination%20letters%20%E2%80%94%20which%20are%20a%20clear%2C%20ringing%20sign%20that%20the%20Justice%20Department%20found%20the%20company%20did%20nothing%20wrong%20%E2%80%94%20remain%20rare.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20USRA%20letter%20was%20in%20the%20works%20for%20years%20before%20it%20was%20issued.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202024%2C%20the%20Justice%20Department%20issued%20only%20five%20declination%20letters%2C%20according%20to%20a%20Business%20Insider%20review%20of%20the%20letters%20posted%20to%20the%20DOJ's%20website.%20(That%20doesn't%20include%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.justice.gov%2Fcriminal%2Fmedia%2F1410761%2Fdl%3Finline%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20special%20counsel's%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20announcing%20he%20declined%20to%20prosecute%20then-President%20Joe%20Biden%20for%20mishandling%20classified%20documents.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20other%20one%20granted%20during%20this%20year%20under%20the%20Trump%20administration%20was%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.justice.gov%2Fcriminal%2Fmedia%2F1410761%2Fdl%3Finline%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELiberty%20Mutual%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20in%20August%2C%20after%20the%20insurer%20disclosed%20to%20the%20DOJ%20that%20certain%20employees%20bribed%20public%20officials%20in%20India%20and%20gave%20up%20%244.7%20million%20in%20ill-gotten%20profits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20pleased%20the%20DOJ%20acknowledged%20our%20proactive%20approach%20and%20affirmed%20our%20commitment%20to%20integrity%20and%20compliance%20across%20our%20global%20enterprise%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20Liberty%20Mutual%20spokesperson%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BWe%20welcome%20this%20conclusion%20and%2C%20in%20addition%20to%20already%20taking%20decisive%20steps%20to%20address%20this%20matter%2C%20will%20continue%20to%20uphold%20our%20values%20and%20act%20responsibly%20everywhere%20we%20do%20business.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEarlier%20this%20year%2C%20Matthew%20Galeotti%3Cem%3E%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Ethe%20head%20of%20the%20DOJ's%20criminal%20division%2C%20provided%20a%20clear%20path%20for%20corporations%20to%20receive%20declinations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20they%20handle%20investigations%20internally%2C%20take%20corrective%20action%2C%20and%20fully%20cooperate%2C%20then%20the%20Justice%20Department%20will%20give%20them%20a%20letter%20saying%20they%20are%20declining%20to%20prosecute%2C%20Galeotti%20said%20in%20a%20public%20speech%20in%20June.%20A%20new%20chapter%20in%20the%20Justice%20Department's%20policy%20manual%20even%20includes%20a%20handy%20flowchart%20to%20help%20white-collar%20lawyers%20understand%20what%20they%20need%20to%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGaleotti%20previously%20told%20Business%20Insider%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.justice.gov%2Fcriminal%2Fcriminal-fraud%2Fcecp%2Fcorporate-enforcement%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enew%20policies%3C%2Fa%3E%20provide%20companies%20with%20clear%20incentives%20to%20voluntarily%20self-disclose%20potential%20wrongdoing%20and%20cooperate%20with%20investigations%20without%20worrying%20about%20coming%20under%20the%20microscope%20themselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20policy%20also%20encourages%20companies%20to%20invest%20in%20compliance%20programs%2C%20which%20helps%20deter%20misconduct%20from%20happening%20in%20the%20first%20place%20and%20detect%20it%20when%20it%20does%20occur%2C%20all%20of%20which%20benefits%20the%20American%20public%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Justice%20Department%20spokesperson%20declined%20to%20comment%20beyond%20Galeotti's%20earlier%20statement%20and%20directed%20Business%20Insider%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.justice.gov%2Fcriminal%2Fcriminal-fraud%2Fcorporate-enforcement-policy%2Fdeclinations%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20list%20of%20several%20declination%20letters%20published%20on%20the%20Justice%20Department's%20website%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.justice.gov%