%3E%3Cspan%3EMy%20parents%20each%20ran%20their%20own%20businesses%20%E2%80%94%20my%20mom%20as%20a%20physician%20and%20my%20dad%20as%20an%20electrical%20engineer.%20I%20knew%20I%20wanted%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstarting-business-husband-works-for-me-boundaries-arguments-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Estart%20some%20type%20of%20business%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20too.%20Having%20money%20saved%20from%20babysitting%20would%20make%20that%20easier.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22271deade-61b5-4887-8fd7-08880ece118d%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EMy%20babysitting%20money%20meant%20we%20were%20profitable%20from%20the%20start%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAfter%20college%2C%20I%20worked%20for%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmom-created-sustainable-clothing-brand-when-she-couldnt-find-one-2022-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ebaby%20clothing%20brand%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20As%20I%20learned%20more%20about%20the%20industry%2C%20I%20realized%20there%20was%20a%20hole%20in%20the%20market%3A%20there%20were%20no%20brands%20helping%20tween%20girls%20make%20a%20soft%20transition%20from%20baby%20clothing%20lines%20to%20young%20adult%20lines.%20I%20decided%20I%20wanted%20to%20create%20a%20brand%20that%20filled%20the%20gap%20between%20smocked%20(baby%20clothes)%20and%20cropped%20(teen%20clothing).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWith%20my%20idea%20in%20hand%20and%20research%20done%2C%20it%20was%20time%20to%20draw%20on%20that%20babysitting%20money.%20I%20used%20%2425%2C000%20to%20register%20my%20business%20and%20launch%20the%20first%20line%20of%20Pleat%20Collection%20in%202021.%20I%20was%2028%20by%20then%2C%20but%20the%20money%20I%20had%20saved%20as%20a%20teen%20allowed%20the%20company%20to%20be%20profitable%20from%20the%20start.%20I%20was%20%E2%80%94%20and%20still%20am%20%E2%80%94%20incredibly%20proud%20of%20that