20forms%20of%20wildlife.%20When%20I%20grew%20up%2C%20I%20automatically%20learnt%20how%20to%20hunt%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Mistry%2C%20in%20a%20conversation%20with%C2%A0%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20everything%20changed%20one%20fine%20day%20in%201990.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAfter%20graduation%2C%20I%20would%20play%20football%20with%20my%20friends%20and%20then%20hunt%20deer%20for%20pleasure.%20One%20day%2C%20when%20my%20friends%20and%20I%20were%20out%20hunting%2C%20they%20shot%20a%20doe%20that%20was%20there%20with%20her%20small%20fawn.%20Seeing%20the%20doe%20in%20pain%20and%20her%20fawn%20in%20tears%2C%20I%20felt%20great%20pain.%20That%E2%80%99s%20when%20my%20determination%20to%20end%20poaching%20began.%20Immediately%20after%20the%20incident%2C%20I%20went%20to%20the%20forest%20department%20and%20met%20the%20then%20field%20director%2C%20Pradeep%20Shukla.%20I%20confessed%20to%20the%20incident%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Mistry.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20response%2C%20the%20senior%20forest%20official%20suggested%20that%20Mistry%20establish%20a%20society%20or%20organisation%20to%20combat%20poaching.%20He%20assured%20him%20that%20the%20forest%20department%20would%20support%20him%20in%20this%20endeavour.%20That%E2%80%99s%20when%20he%20set%20up%20the%20Bali%20Nature%20and%20Conservation%20Society%20(BNCS)%20later%20that%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COur%20objective%20is%20to%20save%20wildlife%2C%20nature%20and%20the%20people.%20In%20association%20with%20the%20forest%20department%2C%20we%20help%20locals%20acquire%20alternative%20means%20of%20livelihood%20so%20that%20they%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20to%20hunt.%20We%20also%20work%20with%20officials%2C%20conducting%20joint-patrolling%20operations%20to%20stop%20poachers%20from%20hunting%2C%E2%80%9D%20informs%20Mistry.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20500px)%20100vw%2C%20500px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F09%2FAnil-Mistry-feature-1-1756722014-500x500.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Anil%20Mistry%20works%20with%20locals%20in%20Sundarbans%2C%20offering%20alternative%20livelihoods%20to%20reduce%20poaching.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F09%2FAnil-Mistry-feature-1-1756722014-500x500.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F09%2FAnil-Mistry-feature-1-1756722014-300x300.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F09%2FAnil-Mistry-feature-1-1756722014-150x150.jpg%20150w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F09%2FAnil-Mistry-feature-1-1756722014-400x400.jpg%20400w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F09%2FAnil-Mistry-feature-1-1756722014-200x200.jpg%20200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F09%2FAnil-Mistry-feature-1-1756722014-96x96.jpg%2096w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F09%2FAnil-Mistry-feature-1-1756722014.jpg%20556w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-494572%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EAnil%20Mistry%20works%20with%20locals%20in%20Sundarbans%2C%20offering%20alternative%20livelihoods%20to%20reduce%20poaching.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Mistry%E2%80%99s%20life%20took%20a%20real%20turn%20when%20he%20met%20with%20Belinda%20Wright%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20Wildlife%20Protection%20Society%20of%20India%20(WPSI)%2C%20soon%20after%20setting%20up%20the%20BNCS.%20After%20meeting%20her%20at%20a%20seminar%2C%20he%20was%20given%20a%20permanent%20job%20with%20the%20WPSI%20to%20oversee%20their%20Sundarbans%20chapter%2C%20conduct%20anti-poaching%20activities%20and%20find%20ways%20of%20offering%20locals%20alternative%20means%20of%20livelihood.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMistry%20shares%2C%20%E2%80%9CLocals%20go%20into%20the%20jungles%20for%20their%20livelihood%E2%80%94fishing%2C%20hunting%2C%20honey%20collection.%20Sometimes%20they%20encounter%20tigers%2C%20which%20are%20in%20their%20natural%20habitat%2C%20seeking%20food.%20Man-animal%20conflict%20is%20inevitable%20under%20such%20circumstances.%20If%20you%20want%20to%20save%20the%20jungle%2C%20you%20have%20to%20reduce%20the%20incidences%20of%20man-animal%20conflict.%20That%E2%80%99s%20why%20we%20are%20working%20with%20the%20government%20to%20offer%20locals%20alternative%20livelihoods%20that%20won%E2%80%99t%20require%20them%20to%20go%20into%20the%20jungle%20regularly.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETheir%20livelihood%20initiatives%20regarding%20sustainable%20agricultural%20practices%2C%20fishery%20and%20veterinary%20sciences%2C%20have%20been%20successful.%20After%20locals%20receive%20training%20in%20their%20respective%20fields%2C%20chicken%2C%20ducks%2C%20fish%20seedlings%2C%20and%20other%20such%20inputs%20are%20given%20to%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20some%20locals%20used%20to%20go%20into%20the%20jungle%20for%20fishing.%20Today%2C%20however%2C%20they%20have%20a%20small%20pond%20near%20their%20home%20where%20they%20are%20breeding%20more%20fish%20for%20consumption%20as%20well%20as%20sale.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAltogether%2C%20they%20are%20earning%20from%20these%20alternative%20sources%20than%20they%20would%20through%20the%20jungle%2C%20without%20any%20real%20risks%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Mistry%2C%20expounding%20on%20the%20benefits%20of%20these%20initiatives.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20it%20isn%E2%80%99t%20just%20the%20WPSI%20involved%20in%20such%20efforts.%20Research%20organisations%20like%20Indian%20Council%20for%20Agricultural%20Research%20(ICAR)%20and%20forest%20officials%20at%20the%20Sundarbans%20Biosphere%20Reserve%20also%20help%20in%20training%20the%20locals%20in%20a%20real%20collaborative%20effort.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20WPSI%20is%20running%20a%20medical%20camp%20where%20we%20distribute%20medicines%20and%20provide%20free%20treatment%20for%20locals%20and%20their%20livestock.%20This%20is%20a%20regular%20and%20collaborative%20process%20with%20people%20from%20the%20area.%20No%20one%20organisation%20can%20do%20this%20work%20alone%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Mistry.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20liaises%20between%20government%20officials%20and%20villagers%20to%20enable%20development%20in%20the%20area%20through%20the%20construction%20of%20brick%20roads%20and%20irrigation%20canals%2C%20and%20the%20provision%20of%20solar%20lights.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20concerted%20efforts%20have%20borne%20real%20fruit%20with%20very%20few%20incidents%20of%20poaching%20reported%20from%20the%20Sundarbans.%20What%E2%80%99s%20even%20more%20remarkable%20is%20the%20change%20in%20behaviour.%20Earlier%2C%20if%20a%20tiger%20strayed%20into%20a%20village%2C%20locals%20would%20try%20and%20kill%20it.%20Today%2C%20they%20inform%20the%20forest%20department%20and%20organisations%20like%20BNCS%20and%20WPSI%20to%20help%20them%20rescue%20it%20and%20release%20it%20back%20into%20the%20wild.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThus%20far%2C%20Mistry%20has%20been%20associated%20with%20the%20capture%20and%20release%20of%2070%20tigers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20800px)%20100vw%2C%20800px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F09%2FWorlds-largest-mangrove-forest-sundarban-bangladesh-Royan-Bengal-Tiger-1-1756722116.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Founder%20of%20BNCS%2C%20Anil%20Mistry%20partners%20with%20forest%20officials%20to%20stop%20poaching%20and%20protect%20wildlife.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F09%2FWorlds-largest-mangrove-forest-sundarban-bangladesh-Royan-Bengal-Tiger-1-1756722116.jpg%20800w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F09%2FWorlds-lar